2 December 2011The Head of the South African Delegation for COP17/CMP7, the Minister of Water and Environmental Affairs, Ms Edna Molewa, together with the Minister of Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries, Ms Tina Joemat-Pettersson, will address the media on the elements of the country s position as well as on climate-smart agriculture initiatives in response to climate change.Details of the briefing are as follows:Date: Friday, 2 December 2011 Time: 15h00 Venue: Yellowwood, on Level 1 of the Inkosi Albert Luthuli International Convention Centre (ICC), DurbanFor enquiries please call: Selby Bokaba Cell: 082 778 0245Issued by: Government Communication and Information System (GCIS)